Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 31? Name Kallikrates. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0147.11.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0586)
